%YAML 1.1
%TAG !u! tag:unity3d.com,2011:
--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: d9bdb2ec858b93b4fb251512417469aa, type: 3}
  m_Name: TalentDatabase
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  talents:
  - name: Air of Authority
    shortDescription: Affect more targets with Test.
    description: "You exude a natural aura of command,\r instilling subservience
      in all around you.\r\n\nOn a successful Command Test, you\r may affect a number
      of targets equal\r to 1d10 plus your Fellowship Bonus.\r\nSuch is the authority
      in your voice that\r even those who are not in your service\r jump to attention
      when you speak. You\r may attempt to get non-servants to\r follow your commands
      by making a\r Command Test with a \u201310 penalty."
    group: []
  - name: Ambidextrous
    shortDescription: Use either hand equally well.
    description: "You can use either hand equally well. You do not take the normal
      \u201320 penalty for making attacks with your secondary hand. \n\n<u>Special</u>\nIf
      you have the Two-Weapon Wielder talent, the penalty for making attacks with
      both weapons in the same Turn drops to \u201310."
    group: []
  - name: Armour of Contempt
    shortDescription: You are resilient to Corruption.
    description: "You drape yourself in the armour of scorn and hatred. \n\nWhenever
      you would gain Corruption Points, reduce the amount you would earn by 1. In
      addition, you may Test Willpower as a Free Action to ignore the effects of
      your accumulated Corruption for one Round."
    group: []
  - name: Arms Master
    shortDescription: "Use non-proficient weapons at \u201310 penalty."
    description: "Such is your skill with a gun that you are able to pick up an unfamiliar
      weapon and use it as though you had trained with it for years. \n\nYou can
      use ranged weapons you do not have training in at \u201310 rather than \u201320."
    group: []
  - name: Assassin Strike
    shortDescription: Attack and move.
    description: "You are like a serene dancer when engaged in combat, leaping and
      spiralling between dismembered corpses like some butcher ballerina.\n\nWhenever
      you engage an opponent and make a melee attack, you may make an Acrobatics
      Test to move at your Half Move rate as a Free Action. \n\nYour opponent may
      not take the customary free attack."
    group: []
  - name: Autosanguine
    shortDescription: Heal 2 Damage/day, always Lightly Wounded.
    description: "Ancient and blessed technology filters your blood. Handed down
      from generations past, your implants repair minor injuries. \n\nFor the purposes
      of healing, you are always considered to be Lightly Wounded. In addition, you
      naturally heal at an increased rate, removing 2 points of Damage each day.
      \n\nYour autosanguinators also soothe the minor pains and sores caused by the
      blessed metal of your implants pressing upon your weak flesh. This has no game
      effect, but does make you slightly less irritable than before."
    group: []
  - name: Basic Weapon Training
    shortDescription: Use weapon group without penalty.
    description: You have received Basic Weapon Training in a group of weapons, and
      can use them without penalty.
    group:
    - Bolt
    - Flame
    - Las
    - Launcher
    - Melta
    - Plasma
    - Primitive
    - SP
  - name: Battle Rage
    shortDescription: Parry while Frenzied.
    description: Despite your frenzied nature, you remain in control when engaging
      in melee. You can spend reactions to Parry while Frenzied.
    group: []
  - name: Berserk Charge
    shortDescription: Gain +20 bonus when Charging.
    description: You hurl yourself at your enemies with reckless abandon, using the
      force of your Charge to add force to your strikes. When you make a Charge maneuver,
      you gain a +20 bonus to Weapon Skill instead of the usual +10.
    group: []
  - name: Binary Chatter
    shortDescription: +10 bonus to control servitors.
    description: You are adept at controlling servitors. Gain a +10 bonus to any
      attempt to instruct, program, or question servitors.
    group: []
  - name: Blademaster
    shortDescription: Re-roll a missed attack, once per Round.
    description: Your mastery of sword and knife is unsurpassed, and your blade always
      strikes true. When attacking with a sword or a knife of any type, including
      chainswords and power swords, you may re-roll a missed attack once per Round.
    group: []
  - name: Blind Fighting
    shortDescription: Suffer half the usual penalties when vision is obscured.
    description: Through years of practice and heightening your senses, you no longer
      need to be able to see your opponents to be able to hit them. You take half
      the usual penalties when fighting in environments that obscure your vision,
      such as fog, smoke, and darkness.
    group: []
  - name: Bulging Biceps
    shortDescription: Remove bracing requirement for certain weapons.
    description: Whereas a weaker man would be sent flying when using powerful weapons,
      your strong physique allows you to remain standing. You can fire a heavy weapon
      on semi- or autofire modes without first bracing.
    group: []
  - name: Catfall
    shortDescription: Reduce falling Damage.
    description: You are nimble and balanced, like a cat, and are able to fall much
      greater distances unharmed than others might. Whenever you fall, you may Test
      Agility as a Free Action. On a success, and for every degree of success, reduce
      the distance fallen by a number of metres equal to your Agility Bonus for the
      purposes of damage calculation.
    group: []
  - name: Chem Geld
    shortDescription: Immune to seduction, resistant to charm.
    description: "A variety of chemical and surgical treatments have rendered you
      immune to the temptations of the flesh. Seduction attempts against you automatically
      fail, and the Difficulty of all Charm Tests made against you increases by one
      step (a Challenging (+0) Test becomes Difficult (\u201310) and so on). When
      you take this Talent, you gain one Insanity Point."
    group: []
  - name: Cleanse and Purify
    shortDescription: Penalty to avoid being hit by your flamer attacks.
    description: "Burn! Burn! Burn! None shall escape your fiery wrath! \n\nTargets
      exposed to your flamer attacks take a \u201320 penalty to avoid being hit."
    group: []
  - name: Combat Master
    shortDescription: Opponents get no bonus for outnumbering you.
    description: Through a combination of reflex and perception, you are able to
      keep many more opponents at bay in melee than a lesser skilled Acolyte might.
      Opponents fighting you in hand-to-hand gain no bonuses for outnumbering you.
    group: []
  - name: Concealed Cavity
    shortDescription: You have a secret compartment on you.
    description: "You have a small compartment hidden upon your person. This might
      be a pouch within your flesh or a chamber fitted into one of your cybernetic
      implants. \n\nYou may conceal one small item, no bigger than the palm of your
      hand, within this cavity. The compartment may be discovered on a Difficult
      (\u201310) Search Test. If the searcher employs additional technology, such
      as a medicae scanner or chem-sniffer, this difficulty is reduced to Ordinary
      (+10)."
    group: []
  - name: Corpus Conversion
    shortDescription: Take Damage to improve Power Roll.
    description: "You can siphon the health of your physical body to fuel your powers.
      \n\nFor every 2 points of Damage you voluntarily take, you may add your Willpower
      Bonus to your Power Roll. \n\nUsing this Talent is a Free Action."
    group: []
  - name: Counter-attack
    shortDescription: Gain free attack with a successful Parry.
    description: "You are skilled at switching from defence to attack in the blink
      of an eye.\n\nWhen you successfully Parry an opponent\u2019s attack, you may
      immediately make an attack against that opponent using the weapon with which
      you Parried. This attack takes a \u201320 penalty to the Test."
    group: []
  - name: Crack Shot
    shortDescription: Deal +2 Critical Damage with a ranged weapon.
    description: "You are able to target your shots at the places where they will
      inflict more harm. \n\nWhen your ranged attack deals Critical Damage, you deal
      an extra 2 points."
    group: []
  - name: Crippling Strike
    shortDescription: "Deal +1d5\u20131 Critical Damage with a melee weapon."
    description: "You are able to land your blows in the spot where they will inflict
      the most harm. Whenever you deal Critical Damage to an opponent using a melee
      weapon, you may deal an additional 1d5\u20131 points."
    group: []
  - name: Crushing Blow
    shortDescription: Deal +2 Damage with a melee weapon.
    description: "Your melee strikes land with force enough to shatter bone. \n\nYou
      add +2 to Damage you inflict in melee."
    group: []
  - name: Dark Soul
    shortDescription: Take half the penalty on Malignancy Tests.
    description: "Your soul is darkly stained, making you resilient to the effects
      of Corruption. \n\nWhenever you are called to make a Malignancy Test, you take
      half the normal penalty. \n\nSee Chapter VIII: The Game Master, page 238 for
      details on Corruption."
    group: []
  - name: Deadeye Shot
    shortDescription: "Called Shots are at \u201310 penalty."
    description: "You always hit an opponent right between the eyes\u2026 or wherever
      else you intended to hit him. \n\nWhen making a Called Shot, you take only
      a \u201310 penalty instead of the normal \u201320."
    group: []
  - name: Decadence
    shortDescription: Gain uncanny resistance to drugs and alcohol.
    description: "Either through mental and physical conditioning or long years of
      abuse, your body has built up a tolerance to chemicals. \n\nWhen drinking alcohol
      or similar beverages, you do not pass out until you have failed a number of
      Toughness Tests equal to twice your Toughness Bonus. \n\nYou also gain a +10
      bonus to tests made to continue using drugs within 24 hours."
    group: []
  - name: Deflect Shot
    shortDescription: You can Parry Primitive ranged attacks.
    description: "You are able to knock aside thrown weapons and shots fired from
      Primitive weapons. \n\nYou may spend a Reaction to Parry an incoming ranged
      attack so long as the attack is from a Primitive or Thrown weapon."
    group: []
  - name: Die Hard
    shortDescription: Re-roll death chance incurred by Blood Loss.
    description: "It takes more than most to finish you off. \n\nWhen you suffer
      from Blood Loss, you may roll twice to avoid death."
    group: []
  - name: Disarm
    shortDescription: Force opponent to drop his weapon.
    description: "You are able to knock your opponent\u2019s weapons from their hands.\n\nWhen
      engaged with an opponent wielding a melee weapon, you may use a Full Action
      to disarm your foe by making an Opposed Weapon Skill Test. If you beat your
      opponent, he drops his weapon to his feet. \n\nShould you get three or more
      degrees of success, you not only disarm him but also take his weapon from him!"
    group: []
  - name: Discipline Focus
    shortDescription: Gain +2 on Power Rolls to manifest discipline powers.
    description: You devote a great deal of time and effort into mastering your Discipline.
      Choose one of your Disciplines. You gain a +2 to Power Rolls made to manifest
      any powers of this Discipline.
    group:
    - Biomancy
    - Divination
    - Pyromancy
    - Telekenetics
    - Telepathy
  - name: Disturbing Voice
    shortDescription: "+10 bonus to Intimidate and Interrogation, \u201310 penalty
      to Fel."
    description: "You have a sinister and upsetting voice. This may be due to infrasonic
      cadences produced by a vox synthesizer, interrogation training, or just an
      inborn air of malice. \n\nYou gain a +10 bonus to all Intimidate or Interrogation
      Tests when you use your voice. You take a \u201310 penalty to Fellowship Tests
      when dealing with persons who are likely to be off-put by your manner (psykers,
      small children, nervous Grox, and so on)."
    group: []
  - name: Double Team
    shortDescription: Gain additional +10 bonus for ganging up.
    description: "You fight best shoulder to shoulder with a loyal ally. \n\nWhen
      ganging up on an opponent with an ally, you gain an additional +10 bonus to
      Weapon Skill Tests. If you both have this Talent, you both gain an additional
      +10 bonus, for a total of +20. \n\nThis bonus is in addition to the normal
      bonuses gained from outnumbering an opponent."
    group: []
  - name: Dual Shot
    shortDescription: One Ballistic Skill Test hits target twice.
    description: "You are able to focus the firepower of two guns to maximize the
      impact. \n\nWhen armed with two pistols, you can fire both simultaneously as
      a Full Action. Make a single Ballistic Skill Test. On a success, you hit the
      target with both shots."
    group: []
  - name: Dual Strike
    shortDescription: One Weapon Skill Test hits target twice.
    description: 'You are able to focus your melee attacks to maximize the impact.


      When
      armed with two melee weapons, you can attack with both simultaneously as a
      Full Action. Make a single Weapon Skill Test. On a success, you hit the target
      with both weapons.'
    group: []
  - name: Electrical Succour
    shortDescription: +10 bonus to Toughness Tests to remove Fatigue.
    description: "You call upon the sacred flow of energy to replenish your weak
      flesh.\n\nWhile in contact with a functioning, powered machine, or a fully
      charged battery, you may make an Ordinary (+10) Toughness Test. If you succeed,
      remove one level of Fatigue, plus one additional level of Fatigue for each
      degree of success. \n\nThis takes one minute of meditation and ritual incantation
      to activate."
    group: []
  - name: Electro Graft Use
    shortDescription: +10 bonus to Inquiry, Tech Use, Common Knowledge.
    description: "You have the ability to use an electro graft to access data points
      and commune with machine spirits. \n\nThis grants you a +10 bonus to Common
      Lore, Inquiry, or Tech-Use Tests while connected to a data point."
    group: []
  - name: Energy Cache
    shortDescription: Luminen Blast, Charge and Shock are Fatigue free.
    description: "You have learned how to focus some of the power stored within your
      potentia coil. \n\nYou no longer gain Fatigue from using Luminen Charge, Luminen
      Shock, and Luminen Blast."
    group: []
  - name: Exotic Weapon Training
    shortDescription: Use an exotic weapon without penalty.
    description: You have received Exotic Weapon Training in a single exotic weapon
      and can use it without penalty.
    group: []
  - name: Favoured by the Warp
    shortDescription: Roll twice for Psychic Phenomena
    description: Whenever a Power Roll triggers Psychic Phenomena, you may roll two
      dice on that table and take the more favourable result.
    group: []
  - name: Fearless
    shortDescription: Immune to Fear and Pinning.
    description: "Whether through fervent loyalty or a derangement of the mind, you
      are impossible to frighten or unnerve. \n\nYou are immune to the effects of
      Fear and Pinning, but to disengage from combat or back down from a fight, you
      must first succeed on a Willpower Test."
    group: []
  - name: Feedback Screech
    shortDescription: 30m radius, Test Willpower or lose Half Action.
    description: "By muttering illogical formulae under your breath, you are able
      to foment rebellion within your vox synthesizers. Your audio circuits protest
      in a screeching blast of noise, shocking and distracting others in equal measure.
      \n\nAll creatures, except Daemonic and machine-based, within a 30-meter radius
      must make a Willpower Test or lose a Half Action on their next Turn as they
      shudder, swear, cover their ears, or otherwise react to the horrid noise. \n\nThis
      is a Full Action and may not be used again for 1d5 Rounds while your audio
      circuits reset."
    group: []
  - name: Ferric Lure
    shortDescription: WP Test to call 1kg/WP Bonus of metal objects.
    description: "You can call an unsecured metal object that you can see to your
      hand.\n\nYou may summon objects of up to 1 kilogram per point of your Willpower
      Bonus. The object must be within a 20-meter radius. \n\nTo use this Talent,
      you must succeed on a Willpower Test as a Full Action."
    group: []
  - name: Ferric Summons
    shortDescription: WP Test to call 2kg/WP Bonus of metal objects.
    description: 'You can call an unsecured metal object that you can see to your
      hand.


      You may summon objects of up to 2 kilograms per point of your
      Willpower Bonus. The object must be within a 40-meter radius. You must make
      a Willpower Test and spend a Full Action to enact this rite.'
    group: []
  - name: Flagellant
    shortDescription: Injure self to gain mental fortitude.
    description: "You have dedicated your pain to the service of the Emperor. \n\nEach
      day, you must spend twenty minutes praying and inflicting 1 point of Damage
      upon yourself. You may not treat this Damage or allow it to be healed. Once
      you have castigated your flesh, you gain a +10 bonus to Willpower Tests made
      to resist mind control or Malignancy.\n\n Additionally, if you have the Frenzy
      talent, you may enter a frenzied state as a Free Action. \n\nShould you fail
      to flagellate yourself on any given day, you take a \u20135 penalty to all
      Tests due to shame and guilt."
    group: []
  - name: Foresight
    shortDescription: Contemplate to gain +10 bonus on next Test.
    description: "You are adept at identifying the consequences of any action. If
      you take some time to consider what you are doing, you can deduce the best
      action for success. \n\nYou may spend ten minutes contemplating a problem to
      gain a +10 bonus to your next relevant Intelligence Test."
    group: []
  - name: Frenzy
    shortDescription: Enter psychotic rage to gain combat bonuses.
    description: "You can incite yourself into a frothing rage. \n\nYou must spend
      one Round psyching yourself up (howling, beating yourself, or injecting psychosis-inducing
      drugs). The next round, you lose control and go berserk, gaining a +10 bonus
      to Strength and Willpower but a \u201310 penalty to Weapon Skill and Intelligence.
      \n\nYou must attack the nearest enemy in melee combat and you may not flee,
      retreat, or Parry. When possible, you must use the All-Out Attack Manoeuvre.
      You remain frenzied for the duration of the combat.\n\nSome creatures, particularly
      certain types of Daemon, do not need to spend a Round inciting the frenzy\u2014they
      are either permanently Frenzied or can Frenzy at will. \n\nUnless you have
      a Talent that allows you to do so, you may not use Psychic Powers whilst in
      Frenzy."
    group: []
  - name: Furious Assault
    shortDescription: On a successful WS Test, gain a free second attack.
    description: "Your blows follow one another in quick succession, raining down
      on your opponents like fiery bolts. \n\nWhenever you hit an opponent while
      using the All-Out Attack Manoeuvre, you may spend your Reaction to make an
      extra attack (this extra attack retains any bonuses or penalties of the original
      attack)."
    group: []
  - name: Good Reputation
    shortDescription: You have a good reputation amongst a certain group.
    description: "You are well respected within your social group or organization.
      \n\nYou gain an additional +10 bonus to Fellowship Tests when dealing with
      this group. This Talent is cumulative with the Peer talent, for a total of
      a +20 bonus."
    group:
    - Administratum
    - Ecclesiarchy
    - Imperial Guard
    - Imperial Navy
    - Inquisition
    - Underworld
  - name: Gun Blessing
    shortDescription: Unjam a number of guns equal to Int bonus in a 10m radius.
    description: "With a wave, you can unjam a number of guns equal to your Intelligence
      Bonus. \n\nYou may bless any weapon within a 10 metre radius. To do so, make
      an Intelligence Test. A success indicates that you have rallied the spirits
      of the weapons.\n\nThis blessing is a Full Action."
    group: []
  - name: Gunslinger
    shortDescription: "Fighting with two pistols incurs only a \u201310 penalty."
    description: "You are ready for anything when you have a pistol in each hand.
      \n\nWhen so armed, you reduce the penalty for fighting with two weapons by
      \u201310. \n\nIf you have the Ambidextrous talent, you take no penalty when
      firing both weapons."
    group: []
  - name: Hard Target
    shortDescription: "Opponents take \u201320 to BS Tests when you Charge or Run."
    description: "The best way to stay alive is to keep on moving, no matter what
      might come your way. \n\nWhenever you Charge or Run, all opponents take a \u201320
      penalty to Ballistic Skill Tests made to hit you with a ranged weapon. \n\nThis
      penalty lasts until the start of your next Turn."
    group: []
  - name: Hardy
    shortDescription: You always heal as if Lightly Wounded.
    description: For the purposes of removing Damage, you are always considered to
      be Lightly Wounded.
    group: []
  - name: Hatred
    shortDescription: Gain +10 bonus to attack hated creatures.
    description: "You have reason to hate one particular race or organization, and
      your malice sharpens your melee attacks. \n\nChoose one race or group from
      those listed above. When fighting opponents that qualify as members of that
      group, you gain a +10 bonus to all Weapon Skill Tests made to attack them."
    group:
    - Criminals
    - Cult (Specific)
    - Daemons
    - Xeno (Specific)
    - Psykers
    - Heretics
    - Mutants
  - name: Heavy Weapon Training
    shortDescription: Gain proficiency with a heavy weapon group.
    description: You are proficient with a specific type of heavy weapon and can
      use weapons of that type without penalty.
    group:
    - Bolt
    - Flame
    - Las
    - Launcher
    - Melta
    - Plasma
    - Primitive
    - SP
  - name: Heightened Senses
    shortDescription: Gain +10 bonus to a particular sense.
    description: "You have heightened one of your senses. \n\nUpon selecting this
      Talent, choose one of the five senses. You gain a +10 bonus to any Tests involving
      that sense."
    group:
    - Sight
    - Sound
    - Smell
    - Taste
    - Touch
  - name: Hip Shooting
    shortDescription: Gain a free attack when you make a Full Move.
    description: "You are able to shoot while on the move. \n\nAs a Full Action,
      you may simultaneously move up to your Full Move rate and make a single attack
      with a pistol."
    group: []
  - name: Independent Targeting
    shortDescription: Fire at two or more targets further than 10m apart.
    description: 'You are skilled enough with firearms to fire in two directions
      at once.


      When firing two weapons simultaneously, you may attack targets
      that are more than 10 meters apart.'
    group: []
  - name: Insanely Faithful
    shortDescription: Re-roll the effects of Shock.
    description: "You take refuge in your madness. \n\nWhen rolling to determine
      the effects of Shock, you may roll twice and take the better result."
    group: []
  - name: Into the Jaws of Hell
    shortDescription: Minions are immune to Pinnng and Fear
    description: "Such is the fervour and loyalty you inspire in your followers that
      they would follow you wherever you lead, even in search of the dread Tyrant
      Star. \n\nWhile you are visible to them, your minions are immune to Fear and
      Pinning."
    group: []
  - name: Iron Discipline
    shortDescription: Minions can re-roll Fear and Pinning Tests.
    description: "Not through mercy and kindness, but through a stern demeanor and
      a sense of justice do you inspire loyalty in your followers. \n\nSo long as
      you are visible to them, your minions may reroll failed Willpower Tests made
      to resist Fear and Pinning."
    group: []
  - name: Iron Jaw
    shortDescription: Toughness Test to overcome Stunning.
    description: "You are made of sturdy stuff and can weather minor blows. \n\nWhen
      you become Stunned, you may make a Toughness Test to shrug off its effects."
    group: []
  - name: Jaded
    shortDescription: Never gain Insanity Points from ordinary horrors.
    description: "You have seen the worst the galaxy has to throw at you to the point
      that you are acclimatized to the worst horrors. \n\nYou never gain Insanity
      Points from the sight of blood, death, or violence, or indeed any mundane horror.
      Supernatural terrors still affect you as normal, however."
    group: []
  - name: Leap Up
    shortDescription: Stand up as a Free Action.
    description: "You are hard to keep down. \n\nYou may stand up as a Free Action."
    group: []
  - name: Light Sleeper
    shortDescription: Count as awake, even when asleep.
    description: "You are a light sleeper and remain alert when most would be fast
      asleep. \n\nYou are always assumed to be awake, even if you are asleep, for
      the purposes of making Awareness Tests, being Surprised, or getting up in a
      hurry. \n\nThe downside is that you often feel tired during the day and as
      a result are grumpy or distracted."
    group: []
  - name: Lightning Attack
    shortDescription: Attack three times with a Full Action.
    description: As a Full Action, you may make three melee attacks on your Turn.
      This Talent replaces Swift Attack. You may not use the Dual Strike talent during
      a Lightning Attack Full Action.
    group: []
  - name: Lightning Reflexes
    shortDescription: Add twice AB to Initiative rolls.
    description: "You react like a flash of lightning. \n\nWhen rolling for Initiative,
      you add twice your Agility Bonus to the roll of 1d10."
    group: []
  - name: Litany of Hate
    shortDescription: Extend benefits of hatred to allies.
    description: "You are so impassioned in your hatred that you can rouse others
      to similar heights of emotion. \n\nAs a Full Action, you may make a Charm Test
      to extend the effects of your Hatred talent to those around you. A successful
      Test grants a +10 bonus to Weapon Skill Tests to one target per point of your
      Fellowship Bonus when fighting your hated foes. The effects last for the duration
      of the encounter."
    group: []
  - name: Logis Implant
    shortDescription: +10 bonus on WS and BS on successful Tech-Use Test.
    description: "You may utilize analytical circuits to calculate trajectory and
      reactions to a preternatural extent. Your ability to read possible outcomes
      lets you anticipate the movement of your opponents. \n\nAs a Reaction, you
      may make a Tech-Use Test to activate your Logis Implant. Note that this uses
      up your Reaction for the Round. Until the end of your next Turn, you gain a
      +10 bonus to all Weapon Skill and Ballistic Skill Tests. Each successful use
      of this Talent causes one level of Fatigue."
    group: []
  - name: Luminen Blast
    shortDescription: 1d10+WP Bonus Energy Damage Bolt. Causes Fatigue.
    description: "With the proper prayer and projection of will, you are able to
      strike at the enemies of the Omnissiah. Using your electoo inductors, you may
      create a crackling ball of bio-electrical energy that you may fling at your
      foes. \n\nOn a successful Ballistic Skill Test, you may direct this energy
      against a single target within 10 metres. The target takes Energy Damage equal
      to 1d10 plus your Willpower Bonus. Each time you use this Talent, you gain
      a level of Fatigue."
    group: []
  - name: Luminen Charge
    shortDescription: Toughness Test to power/charge tech. Causes Fatigue.
    description: "You have learned how to lend your life force to technology. \n\nOn
      a successful Toughness Test, you may use your bio-electrical field to recharge
      or power machinery. This takes one minute of meditation and ritual incantation
      to activate. The Difficulty of the Toughness Test varies depending on the nature
      of the technology, as follows:\n\nOrdinary (+10): \nChemical battery, glow
      globe.\n\n</u>Challenging (+0)</u>\nLas gun charge pack, data-slate, personal
      heater.\n\n</u>Difficult (\u201310)</u>\nOvercharge pack, air conditioning
      unit, servoskull.\n\n</u>Hard (\u201320)</u>\nLand speeder engine, lascannon
      charge pack, servitor.\n\n</u>Very Hard (\u201330)</u>\nIndustrial press, cogitator
      engine, xenos tech.\n\nNote that, at the GM\u2019s discretion, some technology
      is simply too arcane, broken, or power-hungry for you to be able to activate.
      Each time you use this Talent, you gain a level of Fatigue."
    group: []
  - name: Luminen Shock
    shortDescription: 1d10+3 Energy Damage Shock. Causes Fatigue.
    description: "By focusing your bio-electrical energy through electoo inductors,
      you are able to damage your opponents. \n\nYou must touch your enemy for this
      ability to work. In combat, you must either make a successful Weapon Skill
      Test or be Grappling to deliver the blast. Each Luminen Shock deals 1d10+3
      points of Energy Damage.\n\nEach time you use this Talent, you gain a level
      of Fatigue."
    group: []
  - name: Maglev Grace
    shortDescription: Hover 1d10+TB minutes once per day.
    description: "By long hours of rote learning, you have mastered one of the miracles
      of the Omnissiah. \n\nBy spending a Half Action, you may hover 20\u201330 centimetres
      off the ground for a number of minutes equal to 1d10 plus your Toughness Bonus.
      You may move at your normal walking pace and must employ a Half Action each
      round to concentrate on maintaining the rite. \n\nYou may activate this rite
      whilst falling to slow your rate of descent. Treat all falling Damage as 1d10+3
      Impact Damage.\n\nEach Maglev Grace exhausts the power stored in your potentia
      coil, and thus you may only use this rite once in every twelve-hour period."
    group: []
  - name: Maglev Transcendence
    shortDescription: Hover 2d10+TB minutes twice per day
    description: "Devotion to the Machine God has granted you greater knowledge of
      miracles. \n\nAs a Half Action, you may hover 20\u201330 centimetres off the
      ground for a number of minutes equal to 2d10 plus your Toughness Bonus. You
      may move at your normal running speed and must employ a Half Action each Round
      to concentrate on maintaining your rite.\n\nYou may activate this rite whilst
      falling to produce a controlled descent. Provided that this rite is active
      when you reach the ground, you take no Damage from falling. \n\nYou may enact
      this rite twice in every twelve-hour period."
    group: []
  - name: Marksman
    shortDescription: No penalties for firing at Long or Extreme range.
    description: "Distance is no object with a gun in your hand, and you are just
      as adept at picking off far away targets as those nearby. \n\nYou suffer no
      penalties for shooting at Long or Extended range."
    group: []
  - name: Master Chirurgeon
    shortDescription: Perform advanced medical procedures.
    description: "You are trained in the most advanced medical techniques known to
      man. \n\nYou gain a +10 bonus on all Medicae Tests. If you are treating a Heavily
      or Critically Wounded patient, a successful Test heals 2 Wounds instead of
      the normal 1. \n\nIf this character is in danger of losing a limb from a Critical
      Hit (see Chapter VII: Playing the Game), you also provide the patient with
      a +20 bonus to the Toughness Test to resist limb loss."
    group: []
  - name: Master Orator
    shortDescription: Affect x10 more people with a fellowship test
    description: "You are skilled at speaking to large audiences. \n\nYour Fellowship
      Tests and Fellowship-based Skill Tests can affect 10 times the normal number
      of people."
    group: []
  - name: Mechadendrite Use
    shortDescription: You can use a type of mechadendrite.
    description: You have been given the appropriate training, initiation, and hypnodoctrination
      to use a particular type of mechadendrite.
    group:
    - Gun
    - Manipulator
    - Medicae
    - Optical
    - Utility
  - name: Meditation
    shortDescription: You may enter a trance to remove Fatigue.
    description: "By putting your mind at rest and entering a trance, you can repair
      the hurts of your body. \n\nYou must succeed on a Willpower Test. If successful,
      for every ten minutes you remain in the trance, you remove one level of Fatigue."
    group: []
  - name: Melee Weapon Training
    shortDescription: Gain proficiency with a group of melee weapons.
    description: You have received basic training in a group of hand-to-hand weaponry
      and can use them without penalty.
    group:
    - Primitive
    - Chain
    - Shock
    - Power
  - name: Mental Fortress
    shortDescription: Gain protection against psychic attacks.
    description: "You are trained to aggressively resist psychic attacks. \n\nWhenever
      you are the target of a psychic attack, you force the psyker to make a Willpower
      Test. On a failure, the psyker takes 1d10 points of Damage plus 1 additional
      Damage per point of your Willpower Bonus.\n\nThis Damage is considered Impact
      Damage, directed at the head (more specifically, the face). The psyker can
      reduce this Damage by an amount equal to their Willpower Bonus. \n\nThis Damage
      bypasses armour and any Toughness Bonus."
    group: []
  - name: Mental Rage
    shortDescription: You may use Psychic Powers while in the throes of Frenzy.
    description: "You channel your madness and hate into your Psychic Powers. \n\nYou
      may use your Psychic Powers while in a Frenzied state."
    group: []
  - name: Mighty Shot
    shortDescription: Deal +2 Damage with ranged attacks.
    description: "You know how to blast away with a gun to cause the most damage
      to a target. \n\nYou add +2 to the Damage you inflict with a ranged weapon."
    group: []
  - name: Mimic
    shortDescription: You can copy voices.
    description: "You have an extraordinary ability to copy another person\u2019s
      voice patterns. This may be due to implanted vox synthesizers, training, or
      natural talent. \n\nYou must have listened to your target for at least one
      hour in order to study their voice properly. You must also understand their
      language and be of the same race (for example, a human cannot convincingly
      copy an Ork).\n\nListeners must succeed on a Difficult (\u201310) Scrutiny
      Test to realize that you are not the person you are mimicking. If you have
      based your voice patterns on anything other than \"live\" conversations where
      you are in the same room as your target (such as vox recordings or commlink
      conversations), the Difficulty of this Scrutiny Test is reduced to Challenging
      (+0).\n\nNote that this does not make you look like your target; you merely
      sound like them. If a listener can clearly see you are not the person you are
      copying, your deception automatically fails."
    group: []
  - name: Minor Psychic Power
    shortDescription: You gain a Minor Psychic Power.
    description: You have acquired an additional psychic ability. You gain one Minor
      Psychic Power.
    group: []
  - name: Nerves of Steel
    shortDescription: Re-roll failed Tests to avoid Pinning.
    description: "You are able to remain calm, even when bullets fly past and bombs
      fall around you. \n\nYou may re-roll a failed Willpower Test to avoid or recover
      from Pinning."
    group: []
  - name: Orthoproxy
    shortDescription: +20 bonus to resist mind control or interrogation.
    description: "You have learnt to draw mental fortitude from a liturgical circuit
      buried deep within your skull. \n\nYou may \u201Ctune out\u201D mind control
      attempts by concentrating on the prayers recited by the proxy unit. This grants
      you a +20 bonus to Willpower Tests made to resist mind control or interrogation."
    group: []
  - name: Paranoia
    shortDescription: You are alert for danger.
    description: "You are always on the lookout for danger and secretly know that
      the galaxy is out to get you. \n\nYou gain a +2 bonus on Initiative rolls.
      In addition, the GM may secretly Test your Perception to see if you notice
      hidden threats. \n\nOthers, however, may find your constant muttering and twitchy
      looks unnerving."
    group: []
  - name: Peer
    shortDescription: Gain +10 bonus on Fel Tests to interact with organisation.
    description: 'You know how to deal with a particular social group or organisation.


      You
      gain a +10 bonus to all Fellowship Tests when interacting with your chosen
      group.'
    group:
    - Academics
    - Adeptus Arbites
    - Adeptus Mechanicus
    - Adeptus Administratum
    - Astropaths
    - Ecclesiarchy
    - Feral Worlders
    - Government
    - Hivers
    - Inquisition
    - Middle Classes
    - Military
    - Nobility
    - The Insane
    - Underworld
    - Void Born
    - Workers
  - name: Pistol Training
    shortDescription: Gain proficiency with a group of pistol weapons.
    description: You are proficient with a specific type of heavy weapon and can
      use weapons of that type without penalty.
    group:
    - Bolt
    - Flame
    - Las
    - Launcher
    - Melta
    - Plasma
    - Primitive
    - SP
  - name: Power Well
    shortDescription: Gain bonus to Power Rolls.
    description: "Power suffuses your being, allowing you to manifest powers more
      easily.\n\nWhen manifesting powers, you gain a +1 bonus to your Manifesting
      rolls. You may select this Talent multiple times. \n\nIts effects are cumulative."
    group: []
  - name: Precise Blow
    shortDescription: No penalty for attacks against specific Hit Locations.
    description: "You are skilled at making difficult strikes. \n\nWhen making a
      Called Shot with a melee weapon, you do not incur the normal \u201320 penalty."
    group: []
  - name: Prosanguine
    shortDescription: Heal 1d5 Damage once per day.
    description: "By an act of will, you speed the workings of your autosanguinators.\n\nOnce
      every twelve hours, you may make a Tech-Use Test. On a success, you remove
      1d5 points of Damage. \n\nIf you roll a 96-100, however, in addition to failing,
      you overstrain your implants. They cease to function for one week. During this
      time, you are unable to use this Talent and gain none of the benefits of the
      Autosanguine Talent. \n\nOnce the week is over, both Talents are restored.
      Prosanguination takes ten minutes of meditation and ritual incantation to activate."
    group: []
  - name: Psy Rating 1
    shortDescription: Gain powers, roll 1d10+WP bonus for Power Rolls.
    description: "You have unlocked your Psychic Powers. \n\nSelect a number of Minor
      Psychic Powers equal to one-half your Willpower Bonus (round up) from those
      described in Chapter VI: Psychic Powers. \n\nYou gain a Psy Rating of 1 and
      roll one die, adding your Willpower Bonus when manifesting Psychic Powers.\n\n<u>Special</u>\nIf
      your Willpower Bonus later increases, you do not retroactively gain additional
      powers."
    group: []
  - name: Psy Rating 2
    shortDescription: Gain powers, roll 2d10+WP bonus for Power Rolls.
    description: "You have advanced knowledge of Psychic Power. \n\nSelect a number
      of Minor Psychic Powers equal to half your Willpower Bonus (round up). \n\nYou
      now have a Psy Rating of 2 and may roll up to two dice and add your Willpower
      Bonus when manifesting Psychic Powers.\n\n<u>Special</u>\nIf your Willpower
      Bonus later increases, you do not retroactively gain additional powers."
    group: []
  - name: Psy Rating 3
    shortDescription: Gain powers, roll 3d10+WP bonus for Power Rolls.
    description: "Your psychic abilities grow in power and proficiency. \n\nSelect
      one Discipline. Gain one power from this Discipline. \n\nYou also gain a number
      of Minor Psychic Powers equal to one-half your Willpower Bonus (round up).
      \n\nYou now have a Psy Rating of 3 and may roll up to three dice and add your
      Willpower Bonus when manifesting Psychic Powers.\n\n<u>Special</u>\nIf your
      Willpower Bonus later increases, you do not retroactively gain additional powers."
    group: []
  - name: Psy Rating 4
    shortDescription: Gain powers, roll 4d10+WP bonus for Power Rolls.
    description: "You have distinguished yourself by your skill with psychic energy
      and the breadth of your knowledge of Psychic Powers. \n\nGain a number of Discipline
      Powers in any Discipline that you know equal to one-half your Willpower Bonus
      and the same number of Minor Psychic Powers (round up). \n\nAlternatively,
      instead, select one new Discipline and gain one power from this Discipline.
      \n\nYou now have a Psy Rating of 4 and may roll up to four dice and add your
      Willpower Bonus when manifesting Psychic Powers.\n\n<u>Special</u>\nIf your
      Willpower Bonus later increases, you do not retroactively gain additional powers."
    group: []
  - name: Psy Rating 5
    shortDescription: Gain powers, roll 5d10+WP bonus for Power Rolls.
    description: "You are among the most powerful psykors in the Imperium. \n\nGain
      a number of Discipline powers in any Discipline that you know equal to one-half
      your Willpower Bonus (round up). \n\nAlternatively, instead, select one new
      Discipline and gain one power from this Discipline. \n\nYou now have a Psy
      Rating of 5 and may roll up to five dice and add your Willpower Bonus when
      manifesting Psychic Powers.\n\n<u>Special</u>\nIf your Willpower Bonus later
      increases, you do not retroactively gain additional powers."
    group: []
  - name: Psy Rating 6
    shortDescription: Gain powers, roll 6d10+WP bonus for Power Rolls.
    description: "You have reached perhaps the greatest human potential with psychic
      powers and few can compare with your mastery. \n\nGain a number of Discipline
      Powers in any Discipline that you know equal to one-half your Willpower Bonus
      and the same number of Minor Psychic Powers (round up). \n\nAlternatively,
      instead, select one new Discipline and gain one power from this Discipline.
      \n\nYou now have a Psy Rating of 6 and may roll up to six dice and add your
      Willpower bonus when manifesting Psychic Powers.\n\n<u>Special</u>\nIf your
      Willpower Bonus later increases, you do not retroactively gain additional powers."
    group: []
  - name: Psychic Power
    shortDescription: Gain an extra Psychic Power.
    description: You have acquired an additional Psychic Power. You gain one power
      of any Discipline you know.
    group: []
  - name: Quick Draw
    shortDescription: Ready as a Free Action.
    description: "You are quick to the draw, able to have a weapon in your hand and
      ready for combat in the blink of an eye. \n\nYou can Ready as a Free Action."
    group: []
  - name: Rapid Reaction
    shortDescription: Test Ag to negate Surprise.
    description: "You have a hair trigger and react to a change in any situation
      in an instant. \n\nWhen Surprised or ambushed, you may make an Agility Test
      to act normally."
    group: []
  - name: Rapid Reload
    shortDescription: Reduce reload time.
    description: "You have spent so long practising weapons drills that you can reload
      a gun in an instant. \n\nAll reload times are reduced by half (round down)\u2014so
      a Half Action reload becomes a Free Action, a Full Action reload becomes a
      Half Action, and so on."
    group: []
  - name: Resistance
    shortDescription: Gain +10 bonus to Resistance Tests.
    description: "Whether through past exposure, gruelling physical training, or
      luck of genetics, you are highly resistant to a particular thing. \n\nWhen
      you pick this Talent, select a group to be resistant to. You gain a +10 bonus
      when making a test to resist or avoid the object of your resistance."
    group:
    - Cold
    - Fear
    - Heat
    - Poison
    - Psychic Powers
  - name: Rite of Awe
    shortDescription: "50m radius, \u201310 to all Tests due to Fear."
    description: "You may recite an infrasonic liturgy that causes awe and fear.
      \n\nAll humans within a 50-metre radius, regardless of their ability to hear,
      feel a sense of dread and religious guilt. \n\nAlongside these emotional effects,
      all humans take a \u201310 penalty to their next Skill Test. Characters may
      make a Willpower Test to shake off these effects. \n\nWhile incanting the rite,
      you may not talk on any additional frequency. The rite lasts two minutes, and
      it is considered very bad form to break off incantations at any point during
      the liturgy. \n\nNote that humans without auditory implants cannot hear infrasonic
      sound, and thus will assume you are not speaking."
    group: []
  - name: Rite of Fear
    shortDescription: Fear rating 1 for two minutes. 50m radius.
    description: "You may recite an infrasonic dirge, which causes terror within
      the weak. \n\nAll humans, regardless of their ability to hear, within a 50-metre
      radius consider you to have a Fear Rating of 1. \n\nWhile incanting the dirge,
      you may not talk on any additional frequency. The rite lasts two minutes, and
      it is considered very bad form to break off incantations at any point during
      the liturgy. \n\nNote that humans without auditory implants cannot hear infrasonic
      sound, and thus will assume you are not speaking."
    group: []
  - name: Rite of Pure Thought
    shortDescription: You are immune to emotion.
    description: "You have replaced the creative right half of your brain with a
      cogitator. You no longer feel emotion and are instead filled with the cold
      purity of logic. \n\nYou are now immune to Fear, Pinning, and any effects that
      cause emotional disturbance. Others now find you disturbing to say the least.\n\nYour
      GM will remove any Mental Disorders that are no longer relevant and grant you
      new ones of equal severity."
    group: []
  - name: Sharpshooter
    shortDescription: No penalties for Called Shots.
    description: "When making a Called Shot, you do not incur the normal \u201320
      penalty. This Talent replaces Deadeye Shot."
    group: []
  - name: Sound Constitution
    shortDescription: Gain an additional Wound.
    description: "You are able to absorb more damage before you die. \n\nYou gain
      an additional Wound. \n\nIf your advance scheme allows it, you may purchase
      this Talent multiple times."
    group: []
  - name: Sprint
    shortDescription: Move more quickly in combat.
    description: "You are able to put on a burst of speed to get out of\u2014or into\u2014trouble
      fast. \n\nWhen taking the Full Move action, you may move an extra number of
      metres equal to your Agility Bonus. When taking the Run action, you may double
      your Movement for one Round. \n\nIf you use this Talent two turns in a row,
      you gain one level of Fatigue."
    group: []
  - name: Step Aside
    shortDescription: Gain extra Dodge in a Round.
    description: "You are quick at getting out of the way of attacks. You may make
      an additional Dodge once per Round. \n\nIn effect, this gives a character a
      second Reaction that may only be used to Dodge, allowing them to make two Dodges
      in a Turn. \n\nNote that they may still only attempt a single Dodge against
      any one attack."
    group: []
  - name: Street Fighting
    shortDescription: Deal +2 Critical Damage with knives or unarmed attacks.
    description: "You are a master of dirty tricks such as the low punch and the
      knife in the gut. \n\nWhen dealing Critical Damage with an unarmed attack or
      knife, you deal +2 points of Damage."
    group: []
  - name: Strong Minded
    shortDescription: Re-roll tests made to resist Psychic Powers.
    description: "Your mind is like a fortress guarded against psychic attack. \n\nYou
      may reroll failed Willpower Tests to resist any Psychic Powers that affect
      your mind. \n\nPsychic Powers that have a physical effect, such as Telekinesis,
      are unaffected by this Talent."
    group: []
  - name: Sure Strike
    shortDescription: Choose Hit Location on a successful attack.
    description: "You strike with precision, landing your blows wherever you intend
      them to hit. \n\nWhen determining where you hit an opponent with a melee attack,
      you may use the dice as you rolled them or reverse them, choosing the location
      you prefer. \n\nFor example, Beam rolls a 37 to hit an Ork. Ordinarily, Beam
      would strike location 73\u2014the right leg\u2014but because he has the Sure
      Strike talent, he could choose to hit the alien in location 37\u2014the body."
    group: []
  - name: Swift Attack
    shortDescription: Attack twice with a Full Action.
    description: As a Full Action, you may make two melee attacks on your Turn.
    group: []
  - name: Takedown
    shortDescription: Make a special attack to Stun your opponent.
    description: "You are skilled at taking an opponent alive. \n\nAs a Half Action,
      you may declare that you are attempting to Takedown an opponent before Testing
      Weapon Skill. \n\nIf you hit and do at least 1 point of Damage, this damage
      is ignored and your opponent must make a Toughness Test or be Stunned for one
      Round."
    group: []
  - name: Talented
    shortDescription: Gain +10 bonus to corresponding Skill Test.
    description: Choose any one of your Skills. You gain a +10 bonus to Tests when
      using this Skill.
    group: []
  - name: Technical Knock
    shortDescription: Unjam a gun as a Half Action.
    description: "With a honeyed whisper and ritual motion, you can awaken sleeping
      gun-spirits into furious action once more. \n\nYou may unjam any gun as a Half
      Action. You must touch the gun in question to enact this rite. \n\nYou may
      only perform this rite on one weapon per Round\u2014any more would be disrespectful."
    group: []
  - name: Thrown Weapon Training
    shortDescription: Gain proficiency with a group of thrown weapons.
    description: You have received basic training in a group of thrown weaponry and
      can use such weapons without penalty.
    group:
    - Primitive
    - Chain
    - Shock
    - Power
  - name: Total Recall
    shortDescription: Remember trivial facts and minor details.
    description: "Through long years of mental conditioning and practice, your mind
      is like an archive, able to record and recall great amounts of information.\n\nYou
      can automatically remember any trivial fact or piece of information that you
      might feasibly have picked up in the past. \n\nWhen trying to recall more detailed
      or obscure facts, such as the precise layout of a crime scene or a page you
      read in an ancient grimoire five years ago, the GM may require you to make
      an Intelligence Test."
    group: []
  - name: True Grit
    shortDescription: Reduce Critical Damage you take.
    description: "You are able to shrug off wounds that would fell lesser men. \n\nWhenever
      you suffer Critical Damage, halve the result (rounding up)."
    group: []
  - name: Two-Weapon Wielder
    shortDescription: Attack twice when wielding two weapons.
    description: "When armed with two weapons of a particular type, you may spend
      a Full Action to attack with both on your turn. Each Test made to attack with
      the weapons takes a \u201320 penalty (see Chapter VII: Playing the Game, page
      197 for more details). You must take Two-Weapon Wielder (Melee) and Two-Weapon
      Wielder (Ballistic) if you wish to use a gun and hand weapon at the same time."
    group:
    - Ballistic
    - Melee
  - name: Unremarkable
    shortDescription: You are easily forgettable.
    description: "You have a forgettable face and are able to blend in with a crowd.\n\nAttempts
      to notice you when amongst other people or anyone attempting to describe you
      or recall details about you incur a \u201320 penalty."
    group: []
  - name: Unshakeable Faith
    shortDescription: You may re-roll failed Fear Tests.
    description: "Your faith that the Emperor will preserve you is so strong that
      you are unafraid of stepping into danger. \n\nYou may re-roll any failed Willpower
      Tests to avoid the effects of Fear."
    group: []
  - name: Wall of Steel
    shortDescription: Gain an extra Parry each Round.
    description: "Your blades are so quick that they form a wall of impenetrable
      steel.\n\nYou may make an additional Parry once per Round. In effect, this
      gives a character a second Reaction that may only be used to Parry, thus allowing
      them to make two Parries in a Turn. \n\nNote they may still only attempt a
      single Parry against any one attack."
    group: []
